\"creating-a-systemd-service-file\">Creating a systemd Service File<\/h2>\n\n<p>Create a new file with your preferred text editor:<\/p>\n\n<pre>\n<code class=\"code code--source\">$ sudo vi \/lib\/systemd\/system\/hashbrown.service\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>Type\/paste the following into the file:<\/p>\n\n<pre>\n<code class=\"code code--source\">[Unit]\nDescription=HashBrown CMS \nDocumentation=https:\/\/hashbrown.rocks\nAfter=network.target\n\n[Service]\nEnvironment=PORT=8080 (or whichever port you want to run it on)\nType=simple\nUser=username (never root!)\nExecStart=node \/path\/to\/hashbrown-cms\/hashbrown.js\nRestart=always\n\n[Install]\nWantedBy=multi-user.target\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<h2 id=\"reload-the-daemon\">Reload the daemon<\/h2>\n\n<pre>\n<code class=\"code code--source\">$ sudo systemctl daemon-reload\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<h2 id=\"start-the-service\">Start the service<\/h2>\n\n<pre>\n<code class=\"code code--source\">$ sudo systemctl start hashbrown\n<\/code><\/pre>\n            <\/div>\n<\/section>\n                                    <\/main>\n\n        <footer class=\"footer\">\n    <div class=\"container\">\n        HashBrown CMS is licensed under the MIT license<br>\n        Copyright <a href=\"\/\/putaitu.com\">Putaitu<\/a>\n    <\/div>\n<\/footer>\n    <\/body>\n<\/html>\n"}